# Flare Hardhat Starter Kit Rules

This document outlines important information and common commands for the Flare Hardhat Starter Kit, based on [README.md](mdc:README.md).

## Getting Started

1.  **Clone and install dependencies:**
    ```console
    git clone https://github.com/flare-foundation/flare-hardhat-starter.git
    cd flare-hardhat-starter
    yarn
    ```
    or
    ```console
    npm install
    ```
2.  **Set up `.env` file:**
    ```console
    mv .env.example .env
    ```
    Then, change the `PRIVATE_KEY` in the `.env` file to yours. Make sure to add API Keys if needed for deployment.

## Core Commands

*   **Compile:**
    ```console
    yarn hardhat compile
    ```
    or
    ```console
    npx hardhat compile
    ```
    This compiles all `.sol` files in your `/contracts` folder and generates artifacts.

*   **Run Tests:**
    ```console
    yarn hardhat test
    ```
    or
    ```console
    npx hardhat test
    ```

*   **Deploy:**
    Check `[hardhat.config.ts](mdc:hardhat.config.ts)` for network definitions.
    ```console
    npx hardhat run scripts/tryDeployment.ts
    ```

